results.title: My man Jeeves
abstracts: This is a collection of eight short stories which follow the daily routines of Jeeves, Bertie Wooster and Reggie Pepper.

results.title: Little pink riding hood
abstracts: This story, inspired by the well-known classic, is about a greedy wolf who wants to eat a whole basket of cupcakes. He will have to face Little Pink Riding Hood, who confronts him with no fear. A story of kindness, courage, forgiveness and sharing. The book also encourages kids to play with their creativity and imagination, and create toys and costumes by reusing and recycling materials.

results.title: Right ho, Jeeves
abstracts: This is one of the Jeeves and Wooster stories written by P.G. Wodehouse. Set in Britain, the story revolves around the lives of Bertram Wooster and his manservant Jeeves.

results.title: The 30 day exchange
abstracts: This story is about the life of Jonah Walters, who was given up at birth. All he wants is to have a closure on why his biological mother gave him up. However, things are not so simple, as Jonah goes on an emotional ride full of pain, deceit, friendship and love, as he seeks out the answers.

results.title: The fisherman king
abstracts: Lisan, the fisherman always believed he was descended from Bruneian royalty and he wanted to prove it. Returning to the Water Village after eight years, Lisan reconnects with his estranged wife Bathia to recover an underwater treasure that will establish his royal birthright. As the story of Lisan’s true intentions unravels, including what he was really doing in those years away, it becomes intertwined with the ancient history of two doomed royal siblings and a fearsome serpent god called the Nabau.

results.title: Bucky the dino goes green
abstracts: This is a story about Bucky, a big blue dinosaur who loves nature. One day, on his usual trip to the forest, his friend, Mr Robin, nearly choked on the wrapper that Bucky accidentally dropped on the ground. As he flies off and told Bucky "to go green", the learning starts on what it means and how everyone can play a part.

results.title: Breakfast with Lloyd & Liam
abstracts: Cory's younger twin brothers, Lloyd and Liam, are autistic and non-verbal. This is a heart warming story of the family having breakfast at the beach, and how Cory and his parents embrace the twins' special needs, staying positive and supportive of each other.

results.title: First man round the world : adventures of Magellan and Enrique Awang
abstracts: Awang (Henrique/Enrique) befriends Ferdinand Magellan, a Portuguese explorer imprisoned in Malacca. The pair sail to Europe, South America and Asia, encountering numerous challenges on the journey. When Magellan is killed in a battle in the Philippines, Awang is determined to get his freedom and return home.

results.title: The Egyptian codex
abstracts: This is a fictional story involving Michael, a cataloguer of ancient texts, and Anna, scientist. Their adventure to discover some Egyptian fragments began when Michael received a seemingly innocuous manuscript at work.

results.title: Little godwit finds his wings
abstracts: Little Godwit hatches late and finds out that his flock has left to escape the icy cold Arctic. Soon, he meets different birds and tries to fit in with them. Little Godwit has to decide if he would like to stay with these birds or keep flying.

results.title: Do farts make old people go faster?
abstracts: This is part of the series "Jack is curious". Jack, a curious boy, has an idea when his mother explains that Jack is hearing gas escaping from old people when they are farting.

results.title: The yummiest cupcake
abstracts: This children story revolves around Alex and his love of cupcakes. Being only allowed just one cupcake, Alex cannot make his mind up on which cupcake to choose for his birthday. Disappointed Alex receives a pleasant surprise upon getting home. The book also contains various cupcake recipes.

results.title: Can I hit back at a bully?
abstracts: Jack and his best friend Zac are at the playground when three bullies steal their football and call them mean names. Jack wants to use taekwondo to hit back at the bullies but his mother has other idea.

results.title: The movie that no one saw
abstracts: Adjonis Keh is a successful actor with a dark secret: he can’t act. He manages to fool everyone with a clever little trick, until an unexpected friendship with an inquisitive young journalist makes him question everything in his life.

results.title: Impractical uses of cake
abstracts: Thirty-five-year-old Sukhin Dhillon is a teacher at a junior college whose life consists of reading, working and visiting his parents. An errand in Chinatown reunites him with the homeless Jinn, and together they learn about love and sacrifice over their shared fondness for cake.

results.title: What a scare!
abstracts: One night Jeremy mistakes Rubiah for a ghost when she was having her pre-dawn meal for Ramadan. The next day Rubiah and Jeremy investigate odd "ghost" noises in the house. This book is about overcoming fears and cultural exchange.

results.title: End of lies : a political thriller
abstracts: This book revolves around Bob Nolan, a retired CIA officer. After declining an offer from the White House, Nolan decides to reconcile with his estranged wife and children in Singapore. Nolan arrives in Singapore only to find that his wife had moved on. Would he be able to achieve reconciliation with his wife? Or will his involvement with his former colleagues prevent her taking him back?

results.title: Aporia : a novella
abstracts: This is a short story by Singaporean author Clive En-Kai, about a professor, K, who had to confront his past, as well as a Singaporean, Tang, who left his middle-class home to study in a university in England.

results.title: First student's classics : 20,000 leagues under the sea
abstracts: This is a graphic novel adaption of Jules Verne's "20,000 leagues under the sea", which is about the narrator's adventures with Captain Nemo and his submarine Nautilus.

results.title: Gone case
abstracts: This is a novel by Singaporean author Dave Chua. It is written from the perspective of a 12 year-old boy dealing with the life events that happened to him.

results.title: The Zul enigma
abstracts: This is a novel by author J. M. Leitch. The story is set in the future, in 2068, and looks back at a catastrophe caused by a being called Zul, which occurred in December 2012. A woman, who found two survivors of the events, sets out on a quest to find out more about Zul.

results.title: The marvellous sugee cake
abstracts: This is a story about Simon, a seven years old boy and things that happened on his seventh birthday.

results.title: Meet the Wolols : welcome to Wololand
abstracts: This book is about Wolos, a group of joyful characters who aim to engage and encourage kids to play with their creativity and imagination, and create toys and costumes by reusing and recycling materials.

results.title: Make a wish for a unicorn : a book for little girls (and big girls too)
abstracts: This is an interactive picture book to promote imagination and helps children bond with their caregivers and each other by bringing play into reading to help improves their social well-being and learn how to follow instructions, problem-solve, speak with clarity and manage their emotions.

results.title: The Philippine chip
abstracts: This is a story about Gem Putanto, a former King of Coal, in search of his missing fiancée, Princess Anette, who has stolen a quarter of a billion dollars from him. Gem tracks her to the Philippines, where he enters into a deal that he hopes will revive his fortunes.

results.title: Ace agent Spycat and the flying sidekick
abstracts: Spycat is an ace agent extraordinaire from FELINE, a crime-fighting organisation. His latest mission is to investigate and stop the evil penguin king Blackwing who has turned the tropical island of Boracay into his own frozen paradise. But first, Spycat must learn to work together with his new partner, junior agent Rockcat.

results.title: Pinto's pinky promises
abstracts: Pinto loves making pinky promises, but he fails to keep his promises! Pinto apologises to his friends, and makes a pinky promise to make it up to them.

results.title: Saturday's surprisingly super-duper lesson
abstracts: Aish is bored doing maths problems in a classroom on a Saturday morning and she begins to doodle. The drawings come to life and soon the whole class is bubbled over with ideas to create a fantastical roller coaster. This is a tale that showcases and encourages creativity.

results.title: A fickle and restless weapon
abstracts: Zed returns to the island-nation of Tinhau, a homeland he barely recognises. Together with his puppeteering partner Vahid, they decide to produce a lavish production but the opening night is marred by a bombing carried out by a local resistance group. Zed meets Tara, a graphic designer with the Ministry of Culture. Soon they find themselves embroiled in a struggle against a Southeast Asian surveillance state.

results.title: The Java enigma
abstracts: Upon her father's death, Irin Omar inherits a mysterious combination lock, a clue that leads to an ancient map. Together with a retired captain and a dashing salvage diver, Irin goes on an archaeological and historical journey across Asia and Europe to locate the missing pieces of the map, while discovering a few familial skeletons of her own.

results.title: My BFF is an alien
abstracts: This is a story about two thirteen-year-old classmates one of whom is an alien. The efforts of two girls who are the best of friends to find a precious element needed to power the alien's family spaceship are thwarted by their mean classmates.

results.title: This side of heaven : a novel
abstracts: This is a novel about a comedian, a nun, a reality TV star and many others who meet in a garden.

results.title: Theodore and the lady in the purple dress
abstracts: This story tells of the adventures of Theodore, a teddy bear. Theodore was having fun at the fair until he was left behind by Annabelle on a ferris wheel. While trying to find his way home, Theodore came to a shop selling children's clothes and toys. There he saw Annabelle and her parents leaving the shop without Annabelle's baby brother, Brian. Follow Theodore as he tries to rescue baby Brian from being taken by the Lady in the purple dress.

results.title: Mummy loves me
abstracts: This is a book on mother's love. For beginning readers it assures children of their mothers' unconditional love.

results.title: Harris bin Potter and the stoned philosopher
abstracts: This is a story about Harris bin Potter, an orphan with an S-shaped scar. He loves to play void deck football and drink Milo dinosaurs. Upon discovering that he is a wizard, Harris enrols at the MOE-approved Hog-Tak-Halal-What School of Witchcraft and Wizardry where he confronts the most evil spell in the history of magic: Chan Mali Chan.

results.title: The lights that find us : a novel
abstracts: In the novel, Deepavali has never been the same since the terrible mistake Shreya made two years ago. She now dreads the annual celebration, choosing instead to be as uninvolved as possible, until she is visited by three celestial beings who decide to help her right the wrongs.

results.title: Out of order
abstracts: Professor Plano, Zed and Zee find themselves in Lord Myopic's Machiville, a place run by machines. When these machines revolt, Professor Plano and the boys have to figure out how to get the citizens of Machiville out of danger.

results.title: Make animals great again : and other creature campaigns
abstracts: In this children's story, the older animals of Singapore are worried about the deteriorating values of the Next Generation. The animals agree a new leader of the Animal Council is needed to address the issue.

results.title: Kelly and the Krumps
abstracts: This is a story about a teen beset with academic pressures and technology overload. Kelly Mao has got quite the headache: tiger mum, endless tuitions, PSLE, dancing, and her twin brother's troubles with a secret online gaming centre!

results.title: The silhouette in the picture
abstracts: After her parents separated, Donna Cooper lives a life of mere sustenance, taking care of her ailing mother. Now an adult, she seeks revenge, and when her plan fails, she comes up with an alternative plan.

results.title: The royal pup pack : party at the palace
abstracts: Written in honour of Prince Louis on his first birthday and Archie Harrison's arrival, the book celebrates the British royal pup pack of Lupo, Guy, Oz and Jack. Follow the adventures of these royal pups at Prince Louis' first birthday party.

results.title: The brilliant oil lamp
abstracts: Asha and her family move to a housing estate in Toa Payoh and they use an oil lamp to bless their new home. When the power goes out, Asha discovers how the lamp's brilliant light comes in handy, and brings new and old friends together.

results.title: To Japan, with love : a collection of short stories inspired by a visit to Japan
abstracts: National Book Development Council Singapore staff and 23 writing/illustration students from Hwa Chong Institute, LASALLE College of the Arts, Nanyang Academy of Fine Arts, Singapore Polytechnic, School of the Arts, Singapore, and Temasek Polytechnic visited Tokyo and Hakuba Village, Nagano Prefecture in Japan from 13-20 December 2016. In a three-hour workshop for the Japanese and Singapore students popular children’s stories in both countries were shared and new story ideas created. This book is the result of the ideas of the Singaporean students.

results.title: Immortal origins
abstracts: In this story, a 20-year-old Singaporean student and orphan, Jeryl Lee, is plagued by recurring dreams. As he grew older, the frequency of the dreams increased alarmingly. However he is unable to make sense of these cryptic messages.

results.title: Events on 1st Avenue
abstracts: After a car bomb explosion on 1st Avenue in New York City, David finds himself working with an international team of intelligence and security operations to prevent a threat against an upcoming Heads of State Summit.

results.title: Rain
abstracts: This is a novel by author Leigh K. Cunningham, which won the 2011 National Indie Excellence Awards, in the literary fiction category. The story is about the lives of three generations of the Wallin family, set in Australia in the early sixties.

results.title: One fine day there was a frog
abstracts: This is a storybook written by author Terry Moran, for young readers. The story is written in rhymes, with accompanying colourful illustrations. This story is about a frog which invited other animals to tea.

results.title: A man on the moon
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who imagines herself seeing a man on the moon.

results.title: Souls the gods had forsaken : from a 'sex slave farm' in China to a 'death house' in Singapore
abstracts: This is a novel written by Ralph Modder, a veteran Singaporean author, journalist and screenplay writer. The novel is based on a true story, about the life story of a girl who was abandoned at birth in China, and was sold to Singapore as a lady's foster daughter, but was raped by the lady's husband. She then escaped to a "death house" with her daughter, before being rescued by an English woman.

results.title: The fun farm
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a farm which provides fun activities for visitors.

results.title: Sue and her blue shoes
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who was stuck in a patch of glue on her way to school.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 6
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: You are the gun, I am the war
abstracts: This is a fictitious story written by Singaporean author Lisle Tam, about a girl named Lily who lived in Singapore, 20 years after its First Civil War.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 2
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: A snail in a pail
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for young readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who kept a snail in a pail.

results.title: Heaven on earth
abstracts: This is a science fiction written by author Bobby King, in which some humans were killed by aliens when they were escaping from an abandoned town, and which in turn caught the attention of two police officers who wanted to investigate the truth.

results.title: Little Baby Bob
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a baby who loves to play with pots.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 3
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: Different strokes
abstracts: This book is a novel written by Singapore author David Leo. It is a work of fiction, about two AIDS victims who tell their respective sides of the story.

results.title: A star in a jar
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a girl who dreamt that she had a star in a jar.

results.title: Jay, Clay and Ray
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about how a boy with a limp manages to make friends with another boy who keeps bullying him.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 4
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: The Lebouef chronicles : a soldier's betrayal
abstracts: This book, written by author Bobby King, is first of the Lebouef Chronicles, in which the protagonist Captain Lebouef tries to stay alive against an enemy that does not exist in his mind.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 5
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: The mythical emblems of Gragodon. Vol. 1
abstracts: This book, written by Singaporean author Venkataraman Gopalakrishnan, is part of a series of six volumes, known as the Mythical Emblems of Gragodon series. It is of the adventure-fantasy genre.

results.title: Shakespeare can wait
abstracts: This book is a novel by Singaporean author David Leo, about a teacher thinking of his teaching days at a neighbourhood school in the 1970s.

results.title: The big fat cat
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a cat and a rat.

results.title: Ming the king
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about a bully in school who got stung by bees.

results.title: Zombie plantation
abstracts: This book is a fiction novel written by author Lim Meng Yong. The story is set in Muar in the 1940s.

results.title: The little toy shop
abstracts: This is a storybook written by Singaporean author Joanna Wong, for early readers. The story is written in phonetic rhymes and repetitions, with illustrations that she drew. This story is about how a boy manages to get a policeman to catch a robber who has robbed a toy shop.

results.title: Counting numbers 1 to 10
abstracts: Counting penguins. Sing the penguins song. One little two little three little penguins. Counting backwards from 10 to 1. This is a happy counting book for preschool children.

results.title: True greed
abstracts: This e-novel depicts the voracious greed and insidiously scheming ways of the alluring Shanghainese billionairess, Zhang Liyi.

results.title: Water buffalo's reward
abstracts: This is a children's story on a water buffalo who learns that diligence will bring about a bountiful harvest.

results.title: Rainy skies : lull before storm
abstracts: Rain Eveil hates demons to the core, for it was they who burnt her childhood village to the ground, killing all who lived there. But when a beautiful but mysteriously familiar demon invades her dreams, Rain begins to question her sanity. Is there more to her dreams than she realises?

results.title: A myna flies
abstracts: This is a story about power play for land, labour and lives.

results.title: Her silent tears
abstracts: This story revolves around three individuals who experiences the cruelty of this world, who never thought that they would live a life that’s unimaginable.

results.title: The reunion
abstracts: This is a story about Megan Villavieja, a young lady who spent her childhood in Ras Tanura, Saudi Arabia, and now going back to her motherland, Philippines, for a reunion with some individuals.

results.title: Music therapy
abstracts: This book discusses the use of music as a therapy to help improve mental and physical health challenges. This issue contains information on the classification, indication, effect, actual session and origin of music therapy.

results.title: Secrets of Singapore : National Gallery
abstracts: This book offers art-related information such as the various art venues in Singapore, tips on how to appreciate art and well-known Singapore artists. Readers can also join Professor Brushie and Curious Canvas in discovering the fascinating facts and history of National Gallery Singapore, such as secret passages, hidden dome and chocolate ceiling.

results.title: Chop-chop the trishaw
abstracts: Chop-chop the trishaw gets an engine and is now able to zoom fast like the other vehicles. But this does not make Chop-chop happy, so it decides to have the engine removed and goes back to being its old "slow" self.

results.title: Socialism : utopian and scientific
abstracts: Friedrich Engels (1820-1895) was a German philosopher and revolutionary socialist. In this book, he explains the differences between utopian socialism and scientific socialism. He also describes and analyses the ideas of three utopian socialists: Saint Simon, Charles Fourier and Robert Owen.

results.title: The secret of the Tiger's Den
abstracts: The Sengkang Snoopers and their loyal feathered sidekick are having a staycation at Sentosa, and stumble upon a mystery that lands them into mortal danger. Is there a hidden treasure from the Japanese Occupation? Following a harrowing trail that leads them to Tiger's Den, the gang is determined to find out.

results.title: Wagga learns about COVID-19
abstracts: This book contains two parts. In the first part, Wagga learns about COVID-19 and how to fight it. In the second part, upset at being unable to go out often, Wagga learns how to cope with his anger and comes up with a "stay at home" plan.

results.title: Light of the lost
abstracts: A few curiously carved stone tiles set Duncan Beckett and his father on an archaelogical adventure from Algeria to Greenland, tracking discoveries to uncover a lost civilisation. Danger prevails, as they are not the only ones on the trail.

results.title: Lion boys and fan girls
abstracts: This is the sequel to "Lion boy and drummer girl". It is a story about Lion Legends, a lion dance troupe. The troupe finds itself a victim of cyberbullying and then a garbage bomb.

results.title: Diane : a novel
abstracts: Diane is a novel depicting the life of a simple ordinary girl who goes through life's hardships coming from a poor background in India's Karnataka. She loses her father who was her backbone. The story narrates how Diane with her intelligence and strong will-power, fights all the problems she faces, rebuilds her life and marries the man whom she loves dearly.

results.title: The spell of an irresistible woman
abstracts: A historical romantic story about Artemisia, the Queen of Caria, who finds adventure and glory amidst atrocities placed before her. She thrives even when she is taken as a hostage in the Persian land. The story unravels a secret romance and the grace with which she handles her own folly and yet emerges brilliant.

results.title: Yaya the double-decker bus
abstracts: This children's fiction book is about Yaya, the best bus in the country. He is very arrogant that he is number one in speed, looks and height until proven that he cannot do everything.

results.title: Beng Beng revolution : a novel
abstracts: The novel is about Beng Hock and his brother, Beng Huat (who prefers to be called Archibald), find themselves navigating a tumultuous Singapore that has run out of oil and gas. Jobs are scarce, food scarcer and falling afoul of the growing gangs could mean slavery or death. Home for the brothers is a crumbling shanty-town behind the City Hall Steam Engine Station. And if these changes aren't drastic enough, a great power awakens inside Beng Hock and he must learn how to control it before it destroys everyone and everything in his way.

results.title: Matters of the heart : a novel
abstracts: The novel is about Kate and her love life. She had a boyfriend for two long years. Although, the relationship was growing steadily, it was going nowhere. A chance job interview lands Kate a new job where she meets a Casanova who leads a double life. The rest of the story narrates how fate draws them together and their lives get intertwined.

results.title: An unlikely Christmas : a novel
abstracts: The novel is about Penelope and Atticus, who go to the same college. Atticus is a shy dancer who steals Penelope's heart, but she remains in oblivion. She cares for him, yet not willing to accept his love. The rest of the story narrates their roller coaster relationship and whether Penelope accepts Atticus's love.

results.title: Tiene : a novella
abstracts: This is a fantasy novella which depicts how the superheroes, Tiene and his girlfriend, Tienelle, both with magical powers, fight the one-eyed monster, Zora, who has attacked the kingdom of Moda. Moda, was an island on Earth, ruled by King Maya. The King banked on the superpowers of Tiene and Tienelle as the protectors of the land.

results.title: Considered for ruin
abstracts: In this fictional story, Raghav fights his inner demons from his childhood. His past mingles with those of the current situations of Asdhav and Reshma.

results.title: The angel tiger and other stories
abstracts: This is a collection of short stories by Barrie Sherwood. The theme shared by stories is interpersonal relations.

results.title: Just a little bit : a collection of short stories. Vol. one
abstracts: This is a collection of short stories by D. S. Pais. The stories show how destiny contributes towards life under unfavourable conditions.

results.title: Bubble kye
abstracts: Six Tions from planet Tionion. Their mission is to experience life on Earth. This time, Kye, one of the six, tries bubble gum for the first time with unexpected consequences.

results.title: Here we go : let the adventures begin!
abstracts: Six Tions from planet Tionion. Their mission is to experience life on Earth. In this book, the six, Jade, Kye, Indil, Joan, Lara and Ashi discover similarities and differences between Tionions and humans.

results.title: Flowers for no. 29
abstracts: This is a story about two women. One is Toni who returns to Singapore to reconnect with family and friends after ten years in Shanghai while the other is a young lady from China who leaves her country and dreams of playing in a world-class orchestra to work in a place where men wooed the women of their fancy, with flowers worth tens of thousands. Their paths crossed and the two strangers became friends.

results.title: Rays of love
abstracts: This is a short story written by Bruce Chen Choong Fah. It is a romantic fiction about a merman and a mermaid, together with their friends, a manta ray and a stingray.

results.title: Fall of a city
abstracts: This is a short story written by Bruce Chen Choong Fah. It is a romantic fiction about a merman and a mermaid, together with their friends, a manta ray and a stingray.
